# Board Banner & Trim

Route: `/tools/board-banner`. Printable cork-board **hardware polish** (header strips + frame trim), not content posters.

## Print model
- Portrait **pack sheets**: letter 8.5×11 (default) or tabloid 11×17
- Multiple short pieces per sheet with **printed** dashed cut marks inside the capture node
- Banner / top / bottom strip heights: 2.5″ / 3.5″ / 4.5″; side/corner edge widths: 1.5″ / 2″ / 2.5″
- Export captures the pack sheet only (PNG + PDF)

## Frame kit (locked)
- Kit pieces: **Top**, **Side**, **Bottom**, **Corner** — all optional toggles
- Default: top + side + bottom, **corners off** (continuous full-edge rails that butt together)
- Corners on = L-miter tiles for joints; corners off = border runs the whole distance
- At least one piece must stay on (cannot clear the kit)
- **Top** uses header banner layouts (`BoardBannerCanvas`) so the loop includes banner art inside trim
- Standalone **Header banner** mode still exists for banner-only packs
- Export: one pack sheet per selected piece type (multi-page PDF / ZIP of PNGs)
- Side/bottom = dual-tone rails with end caps; corner = L-miter tiles

## Chevrons — deferred (do not reintroduce casually)
- **No chevrons** in current banner or trim art
- Chevron *geometry* can look strong later as pure motif (Local 124–style)
- What failed: forcing chevrons **with** LOCAL / byline type on narrow rails — cramped font + overlay looked bad
- If revived: treat as optional **decoration only**, never under/over body copy on thin strips; keep type on solid end caps

## Shared ornaments (banner + trim)
One Ornaments section applies to both modes:
- Show local number
- Logo: `none` | `lockup` | `mark` via `BrandLogo variantOverride`
- Show byline + editable byline text (seed from Brand Kit `subText` once; **never** hardcode a union slogan)

## Multi-union
- No union names or slogans in core layout code — Brand Kit / user copy only
- Colours from Brand Kit / ThemePicker; logo from Brand Kit

## Capture-safe colours
Follow `.cursor/rules/comms-module.mdc`: inline hex inside capture nodes; `pickContrastingInk` / `BrandLogo backgroundColor={…}`; keep UI shadows outside `canvasRef`.
